Text: After our team was formed, we quickly had some zoom sessions to determine what projects we wanted to do.
We managed to get project pitch done and did a decent job in the client interview as they were chatty and willing to help us with any questions we had.
I am in a much different team this time around and it has taken a while to get used too.
The good side of being in a new team is that a lot of my team mates are quite strong technically and always have ideas to tackle different issues we might face.
Most of my team mates are also quite easy going so decision making has been fast compared to my last group.
UnfortunatelyÂ there have been some issues related to communication already with some of my team.
For example, we decided to have a zoom session the day after the project pitch to discuss the questions we were going to ask the client.
I went on zoom at the scheduled time and but no one was on so I messaged everyone to see where they were.
This led to me being on zoom alone for 40 minutes trying to get in touch with everyone to remind them that we had a meeting schedule for that day.

I managed to get two of them on, but my frustration was also compounded by that fact that one of my team mates told me I should have sent out a reminder for the meeting, even though we had all agreed to it.

I've had other similar experience's this week regarding people not responding to messages to meet up to do group work, so I am concerned that some of my teammates are having trouble dealing with their work or are not overly committedÂ to the project.

To address these issues next week I will try doing things like sending reminders to my teammates for any meetings and then possibly follow up individuallyÂ with people if they are not respondingÂ to our group messaging platforms.
I could also figure out how many things they have outside the project at the moment to get an understandingÂ of why they are not communicating with the team.
Goals for the project and next week.
My main three goals this project are:
1.Get more experience using API's to collect information from websites
2.Possibly learn more about databases, although we may not use it in our project
3.Learn more about using python and an additional language like JavaScript.
Next week I hope to get our project pitch and proposal done, clarify our tools for the project and help improve the overall team communication.
